        "canonical_link": null,
        "text": "Berlin will be more open with far more side quests\n\nWhile I've seen plenty of good folks tell others in threads about this, it is clearly not reaching people well enough.\n\nLink to the thread about it on official forums: http://www.shadowrun.com/forums/discussion/28437/berlin-is-more-like-genesis-game-more-open-world/p1\n\nSeattle is more of a personal introduction to the game/world.\n\nLinear due to being focused on one, straight narrative.\n\nBerlin is more traditional Mercenary Shadowrun.\n\nBerlin will feature many clients with many quests, not a linear story-driven experience.\n\nFor those that enjoy the foundation of the game, but not the focused linear style of this \"Story\", I'd keep my eye out on what happens with Berlin.\n\nI think this is a place where the way you look at this game can have an impact on your experience. I have viewed this first campaign in the way I view episodic games. \"The Dead Man's Switch\" is basically one episode, not what one should call the entire purchase. The editor is extremely powerful, and given time many of the player made stories will offer a great deal of options tailored to various tastes. If you liked the core gameplay enough and even if you feel dissatisfied with your purchase, my suggestion is to stick it back on the virtual shelf for now, and see what the workshop/Berlin has to offer you in a few months time."
